                           <locus target="#1r">Fols. 1r-2</locus>v, 76rb-77v: Excerpt form ʾAnqäṣä nǝssǝḥa “The Gate of Penitence”.<q xml:lang="gez">Fol. 1v: ንዌጥን፡ በረድኤተ፡ እግዚአብሔር፡ አንቀጸ፡ ንስሐ፡ ዘተቀድሐ፡ እም፹ወ፩፡ መጻሕፍት…</q>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           The text is carelessly written in a poor hand. It beginns on fol. 1v and is incomplete (cf. Vat. Aeth. no. 156).
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- Tämälläs-signs, in the shape of a cross, indicating the place where the omissions written in the margins, in the main hand, belong: fols. 16vb l.4, 45va l.11.  &#xD;
- Omitted words are written interlineally, in the main hand: fols. 17ra, 20rb, 49ra, 53vb.&#xD;
- On numerous fols. the scribe aimed at accomodating bigger portions of the text within 18 ruled lines. Due to that he often disregarded the ruling: fols. 17v, 18rv, 31va, 35v, 43v, 61v, 62r, 63r, 64r, 69r.&#xD;
- Recent scribbles and writing exercises: fols. 1r, 35v, 36r.</item>
                     </list>
